Comments: This is from soil crust (microbial communities living in the soil surface in the dryland system). This is a valuable data with time series. So I suggest let's first look at how abundances are different relevant to other bulk soils samples nearby (bulk soil samples means soil sampling at a certain depth). As soil depth is one feature in your data, you can include this site data by labling the depth =0 ). This may indicates that how soil curst showed different compared with other soils depths, associated with EFC distribution
column16: Also, as your manuscript version of the model don't have soil moisture as a prediciton feature, I worry your model may not be able to simulate the change in EFC in resposne to time after wetting events.
